# Post-merge — sync local main

When a plan2026 PR is merged (you merged it, babysit finished, or the user asks if it merged), **immediately** sync local `main`. Do not wait for the user to request this.

```powershell
cd c:\Users\Admin\Desktop\vscode\plan2026
git fetch origin
git stash push -u -m "WIP before post-merge main pull"   # only if checkout blocked
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git log -3 --oneline
```

- If you stashed WIP, tell the user (`git stash list`; `git stash pop` to resume).
- Merged PRs with a changeset should show `chore: version packages [skip ci]` on `main` after pull.

Full workflow: **create-pr** skill §10 and `AGENTS.md`.
